rComments: There a lot of material covered in this course, perhaps a bit too much for this level, but the exams are doable if you're prepared, so it's fair. The lectures are very full and demanding, but interesting anyways. He clearly only cares that you are there to learn, and so he's kind of looking out for those who do want to learn the material.
It's an experience for sure, but he knows the material, wants you to learn what he tries to show is interesting. I enjoyed it a lot.
This prof is great for the brighter students, but not too good for those who probably should think about dropping the course. He knows his stuff and seems to expect students to be self-motivated.
